text: The CAMS Enterprise™ Student Portal is a powerful, easy-to-use tool that offers the highest level of security to ensure the confidentiality of students’ sensitive data. Students can register online, check their grades, and submit resumes online anytime, anywhere.
Special highlights of the CAMS Enterprise™ Student Portal include:
The Student Portal is an integrated part of CAMS Enterprise™ sharing the data and programming of the system for complete consistency.
Students can update their own basic information–each institution has the full decision-making power in determining which, if any, address can be changed (such as local, home, etc.).
View student directory online with email link readily available. (Only those students who have provided the appropriate release information will appear in the directory.)
View scrolling news specific to your institution.
Access calendar to view Miscellaneous Events, Registration Dates.
Provide unlimited links to sites valuable to your student body.
Faculty Portal that is truly cross-platform, eliminating common accessibility issues.
Features of the CAMS Enterprise™ Faculty Portal include:
Allows faculty to enter the basic demographic information such as address, phone number, activities, and education.
Generate a faculty directory easily. Email other faculty members on the fly.
Ability to print directory of their own advisees.
Automated link to Blackboard, WebCT or other in house program to create and maintain course content or use the built-in course management.
Enter and modify office hours. This information can be viewed through the student portal as well.
Faculty will be able to print their own up-to-date class rosters.
Access calendar to view Miscellaneous Events, Registration Dates and Deadlines, Institution Activities, and more…
The registration process will be permitted for their own advisees only.
Display open registration student or advisors, dates specific for Senior, Junior, Sophomore and Freshman registrations, last day for drop, etc.
View course master including the Description, Prerequisites, Co-requisites.

Register students with automatic checks for time conflicts, repeats, pre-requisites and co-requisites, class capacity (with ability to add to a wait-list). Students with a predetermined degree audit can be limited to courses that should be taken based on the degree requirements.

It is the goal of SAU to produce scholars who thrive in the classroom, and then use that success as a foundation for continued study or a career. With dedicated faculty, stimulating coursework and a number of resources, students receive the support they need to achieve academic excellence.

We begin with the end in mind at SAU. No matter where our students start, they end with a sense of ownership over their futures, and the confidence to pursue the next step in their lives boldly. Through career counseling, workshops, and mentorship, our scholars are shown how to be leaders of tomorrow.
Programming, extracurricular organizations and exposure to the arts provide students with a transformational experience.
With strong Episcopalian roots, SAU keeps spirituality at the heart of all University functions and encourages spiritual growth in its student body.
SAU students are encouraged to maintain proper health and wellness. Facilities and services are made available to ensure they evolve into healthier adults.
WHAT MAKES A VISIT TO THE OFFICE OF CAREER COUNSELING & PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT WORTH YOUR WHILE?

mission is to empower students to identify and maximize the connection between what they learn and how they make a living. Ultimately, it is crucial for students to self-manage their own lifetime career development. To that end, we offer comprehensive services to facilitate self-assessment, skill identification, career exploration, decision-making, and career preparation and graduate school selection. Partnering with faculty, staff, alumni and employers we seek to guide students toward active citizenship in an interdependent world through productive and satisfying work.

We help students become employed. We have successful, on-going relationships with employers on the local and state levels and several private industry companies as well. Our students and graduates have been interned or gained full-time employment with organizations from the Office of the Governor of North Carolina to Nationwide Insurance to NC Correctional Institution for Women to Fox and ABC News to name a few! Every student at Saint Augustine’s University is introduced to career readiness as early as freshman year, and each graduate candidate is required to complete a series of professional development seminars and competencies to be eligible for graduation.

University Central Network is an on-line job search engine for employers to view our alumni and student resumes for internships, part-time, and full-time employment opportunities. Our students can also utilize this service for their benefit of meeting perspective employers and future opportunities.

These services include online resume referrals, on-campus recruiting, job fairs, online job listings, and special focus programs that provide unique opportunities to interact with our many talented graduates.
Learn how to answer interview questions and convince the hiring manager that you are the one for the job, practice good nonverbal communication and dress for the job or company.

A qualified career counselor will help in a number of ways: Help to refocus on what's important and zoom out on what isn't, accurately assess skills and potential, clarify values and goals and match work with core values.
These services include online resume referrals, on-campus recruiting, job fairs, online job listings, and special focus programs.
Saint Augustine's Work Study opportunity is a federally-funded program that helps students earn financial funding through part-time employment.
The Professional Development and Career Services Center strives to expose students to various opportunities to career experience before they leave the gates of Saint Augustine's University.
